review_blob:
Good beer, subtly hoppy. No heavy after taste, and paired well with Mexican cuisine. Glad to support local brews.

beer_name: Great South Bay Tasting Room Exclusive #06: Robert Moses Blood Orange Pale Ale

review_blob:
Lively carbonation, but wasn't a fan of the hoppy after taste, even though it was mild. Pours like orange liquid gold, with a floral aroma. Overall, not too bad, but not the best Saison I've had.
